The paper deals with a new set of multigraph parameters that are relevant for problems in number theory and multigraph algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The paper also discusses reduction rules for hyperelliptic graphs, which are relevant to Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions recognizing hyperelliptic graphs in polynomial time, which could fall under Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) or Symbolic Computation (cs.SC). Finally, the paper provides algorithms for recognizing hyperelliptic graphs, which could also fall under the category of Software Development (cs.SD).
